        "title": "fix(cli): validate gateway RPC timeout inputs",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Repair #54646 on its existing contributor branch.\n- Align Gateway RPC omitted-timeout fallback with the 30000 ms CLI default.\n- Reject malformed and explicit empty Gateway RPC --timeout values instead of silently falling back.\n- Validate explicit cron add --timeout-seconds values so invalid input fails at the CLI boundary.\n\n## Credit\nCarries forward #54646 by @ruanrrn and preserves the earlier timeout-validation context from #40953.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm check:changed\n- pnpm -s vitest run src/cli/gateway-rpc.timeout-option.test.ts\n\n## Out of scope\n#60661 accepted-run timeout ownership semantics are related but separate and should not be included in this repair.\n\nClownfish 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: ghcrawl-207037-agentic-merge\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/54646, https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/40953\n- Credit: Preserve @ruanrrn as the original #54646 contributor; repair the existing branch because maintainer_can_modify=true.; Keep #40953 by @comeran in the historical attribution if the final merge notes mention the earlier broader timeout-validation attempt.; Do not borrow #60661 accepted-run timeout semantics in this repair; that branch is related but blocked by separate product-direction and build/runtime review findings.\n- Validation: pnpm check:changed; pnpm -s vitest run src/cli/gateway-rpc.timeout-option.test.ts\n- Repair fallback: source PR #54646 is a fork branch requiring rebase; use replacement branch because GitHub App pushes to contributor forks can be rejected when rebased upstream history includes workflow files\n\nfish notes: model gpt-5.5, reasoning xhigh; reviewed against aeda3bcecdde.\n",
